text:
 @fatemehhamounpou1815 thanks! I think the infrastructure is there, that’s why Apple has been introducing the SOS and satcom texting over the last generation. The most complicated part will be calls/data, as soon as those are integrated, they’ll shred any modern chipset and drain the battery. I work with some pretty insane radios and if we are doing satcom calls or data, the battery (about a colossal 30,000 mAh) is drained in about 15 minutes.

For pricing, I would imagine it would be priced a little above current phone plans however I wouldn’t be surprised if Apple started releasing satcom version, cellular version and a more expensive satcom/cellular. This will lock people in even more. 

This is all theory tho!
